The paper presents a tool for generating unit tests for Java classes specified in JML, which is a specification language for Java. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the tool uses random generation of test cases, which is a technique commonly used in Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the use of weights to control the random aspect of the tool, which is a technique commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
